author: David Ruse
title: WWE Smackdown: John Cena learns his Elimination Chamber opponents | WWE News | Sky Sports
text:
Book WWE's February 12 PPV on Sky Sports Box Office 
Styles, The Miz and reigning Intercontinental Champion Dean Ambrose have all held a WWE world title before, but Wyatt and Corbin will be hoping to land the top prize for the first time when they compete in the Chamber, live on Sky Sports Box Office later this month. 
Wyatt's inclusion sets up the intriguing possibility of a WrestleMania bout against his stablemate Orton, who booked his main-event spot at The Show of Shows by lastly eliminating Roman Reigns at last weekend's 30-man, over-the-top-rope clash in San Antonio. Randy Orton has won the Royal Rumble twice 
Wyatt and Orton teamed up on Tuesday's edition of Smackdown to defeat Cena and Luke Harper, the latter now seemingly excommunicated from The Wyatt Family having attacked Wyatt and Orton during the Rumble Match. 
Orton pinned Cena after hitting his trademark RKO but The Cenation Leader will get a shot at revenge on next week's show when he goes one-on-one with The Viper in a non-title bout. John Cena was confronted by The Wyatt Family as he discussed winning his 16th world title at WWE Royal Rumble 
Cena's Elimination Chamber rivals also came to blows, shortly after Styles had beaten Ambrose in the main event following The Lunatic Fringe's decision to take out Corbin and Miz at the commentary desk. 
Meanwhile, Naomi and a raft of tag teams learnt that they would receive title opportunities against Alexa Bliss and American Alpha respectively at the Elimination Chamber pay-per-view in Arizona. Naomi (R) will battle Alexa Bliss at Elimination Chamber 
Naomi pinned Smackdown Women's Champion Bliss for the second time in three nights while teaming with Becky Lynch against The Wicked Witch of WWE and recent returnee Mickie James. 
American Alpha issued an open challenge for their Smackdown Tag Team Titles, with The Usos, The Vaudevillains, Breezango, The Ascension , and Heath Slater and Rhyno all heading to the ring and engaging in a brawl . Will American Alpha retain their belt later this month? 
Chad Gable and Jason Jordan will now defend their straps - which they won from The Wyatt Family on the final Smackdown of 2016 - against the five teams in a Tag Team Turmoil Match on Sunday week. 
Elsewhere, Carmella downed Delilah Dawson after James Ellsworth tripped her opponent up, while Dolph Ziggler's attempts to rip off Kalisto's mask after defeating him were foiled by Apollo Crews. 
Missed WWE Smackdown? Catch the repeat showing at 10pm, Thursday, Sky Sports 5. WWE Late Night Smackdown
